SIMPLE: materia_medica
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Materia medica
<hw>Ma*te"ri*a med"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. See
<er>Matter</er>, and <er>Medical</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Material
or substance used in the composition of remedies; -- a general term for
all substances used as curative agents in medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That branch of medical science which treats of the
sources, nature and properties of all the substances that are employed
for the cure of diseases, primarily with natural preparations, rather
than pure or synthetic medicines; pharmacognosy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Materiarian</ent>⟦br⟧
